#Summary1=(human1) On Jan. 10, 1970, Marcie writes to her mum worrying about acceptance to colleges, for which she needs two more $15 checks for Wesleyan and Syracuse, telling her about a family picture she made for creative days with her camera, and discussing her expenses, for which she asks for $20-25 a month.

#Summary2=(human2) Marcie writes to her mother concerning her financial and academic concerns and the extra-curricular events of both the previous few days and the following months, including creative days, monthly expenses, and school acceptances.

#Summary3=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) On January 10, 1970, Marcie writes to her mother discussing creative days at school, requesting expense checks, thanking her for grapefruit, suggesting monthly allowance arrangements, describing a responsibility day event, sharing camera troubles, and expressing anxiety about Wesleyan admissions.

#Summary4=(gpt4o) On January 10, Marcie writes to her mother expressing frustration about the timing of creative days after vacation, updating on her expenses and the delicious grapefruits she received, discussing "responsibility day" and her struggles with photography, sharing concerns about her acceptance to Wesleyan, and sending love to family members including a mention about Kittie.

#Summary5=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct) Marcie writes to her mom about her struggles with creativity, using a new camera, and expressing concerns about upcoming responsibility events and her chances of getting accepted at Wesleyan.
#Text=19 70
#Text=Jan. 10
#Text=dear mum ,
#Text=sure enough we had creative days these past two days .
#Text=Frankly I think it was one of their biggest mistakes ; to make them be so soon after vacation .
#Text=I was n't creative at all , but did catch up on my sleep .
#Text=I forgot to get two more checks from you .
#Text=Both are for $ 15 , one is Wesleyan and the other is Syracuse .
#Text=The grapefruit apparently arrived before vacation , but smart Mrs. Bonde put them in the big kitchen refrig.
#Text=I 've already had 5 out of the 9 .
#Text=Boy , were they delicious !
#Text=wish i could have more ? !
#Text=About my expenses .
#Text=I 've been thinking that $ 20 - $ 25 per month would be fine .
#Text=Why do n't you just give me $ 130 in a lump or send me a monthly check .
#Text=I prefer the latter .
#Text=Last Wed. was responsibility Day .
#Text=We had discussion groups about the hand book and certain situations .
#Text=I really wish they 'd waited for the creative days ; in the middle of Feb. I would have been ready for them , and would have done something very creative .
#Text=I did the picture of the family and I 'm so mad ‘cuz only 1 came out .
#Text=I ca n't under stand it .
#Text=I still do n't know how to work that camera .
#Text=It all has to do with the speed and shutter settings .
#Text=One was n't slow enough & the other was n't open op enough .
#Text=Hopefully I 'll get more on the next roll .
#Text=I ca n't believe we 've got achievements . today .
#Text=Oh , eck !
#Text=I heard from Adelle that already 25 have been accepted at Wesleyan , that leaves 75 more , I already know of 6 kids ten times more competent than I , who are applying .
#Text=Rats !
#Text=got ta go now .
#Text=give my love to all , say " hullo " to Wila .
#Text=Love ya .
#Text=Marcie
#Text=P.S. What about Kittie ?
